The paper focuses on deep learning-based object detection frameworks, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses various deep learning models and their optimization functions, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper provides experimental analyses and comparisons of various methods, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
